From: Andy Alt <arch_stanton5995@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 19:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] tests: tag network-dependent tests with suite 'network'

test_connect and test_ipv6 dial github.com:80 and a hardcoded GitHub
IP, so they require network access. Sandboxed builds (OBS, sbuild,
mock) can now exclude them via `meson test --no-suite network`.

Backport of upstream change scheduled for v0.2.3.
---
 tests/meson.build | 10 +++++++++-
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/tests/meson.build
+++ b/tests/meson.build
@@ -17,6 +17,10 @@ test_cases = [
   'ttybuf',
   ]

+# Tests that dial out to public hosts; excluded in sandboxed builds
+# (e.g. OBS, sbuild) via `meson test --no-suite network`.
+network_cases = ['connect', 'ipv6']
+
 foreach case : test_cases
   name = 'test_' + case
   exe = executable(
@@ -29,7 +33,11 @@ foreach case : test_cases
     c_args : ['-DUSE_AS_TEST_LIB', '-DM2K_SUPPRESS_DEPRECATED'],
     dependencies: [dep_modemu2k]
     )
-  test(name, exe)
+  if case in network_cases
+    test(name, exe, suite: 'network')
+  else
+    test(name, exe)
+  endif
 endforeach

 python3 = find_program('python3', required: false)
